# 🚀 Go (Golang) Learning Roadmap

This repository documents my journey of learning Go from beginner to advanced, including concepts, practice code, and projects.

---

## 🔹 Phase 1: Fundamentals (Current Stage)

### 📚 Topics
- Variables & Data Types                        DONE
- Control Flow (`if`, `for`, `switch`)          DONE
- Functions                                     DONE
- Arrays, Slices, Maps                          DONE
- Structs                                       DONE

### 🎯 Goal
Write basic programs without confusion and understand core syntax.

---

## 🔹 Phase 2: Core Go (Very Important)

### 📚 Topics
- Pointers                                      DONE
- Methods (Value vs Pointer Receiver)           DONE
- Interfaces ⭐                                DONE
- Error Handling (`error`)                      DONE
- Packages & Modules                            DONE
- File Structure                                DONE

### 🎯 Goal
Understand how Go is designed and how real programs are structured.

---

## 🔹 Phase 3: Concurrency (Go’s Superpower ⚡)

### 📚 Topics
- Goroutines                                    DONE
- Channels                                      DONE
- `select`  
- `sync.WaitGroup`  
- Mutex                                         DONE

### 🎯 Goal
Write safe and efficient concurrent programs.

---

## 🔹 Phase 4: Real Backend Development

### 📚 Topics
- HTTP Servers (`net/http`)                     DONE
- REST APIs  
- JSON Handling  
- Middleware  
- Logging  

### 🛠️ Projects
- Simple API  
- Authentication System  
- CRUD Application  

### 🎯 Goal
Build real-world backend systems using Go.

---

## 🔹 Phase 5: Advanced Go

### 📚 Topics
- Context (`context.Context`)  
- Memory Optimization  
- Garbage Collection  
- Profiling (`pprof`)  
- Reflection (Basics)  

### 🎯 Goal
Understand performance and internal working of Go.

---

## 🔹 Phase 6: Production Level

### 📚 Topics
- Project Structure (`cmd`, `pkg`, etc.)  
- Testing (`go test`)  
- Docker  
- Deployment  

### 🎯 Goal
Build production-ready, scalable Go applications.

---

## 🔥 Learning Approach

- Practice daily  
- Build small projects  
- Focus on concepts, not just syntax  
- Break and debug code to learn faster  

